HEADWORD: Impoundage
<hw>Im*pound"age</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m*pound"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of impounding, or the state of being
impounded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fee or fine for impounding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impounder</ent>⟦br⟧
